<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="pn1021k"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="pn1" href="#pn1021">PN1: </a>  <a href="../../FF/unbs/pn1all.htm#pn1021k"> (II.A) 21(k)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> His pride and hatred of his race</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">In this, too, he was misunderstood, in his humility for, though it is true &ldquo;that humiliated pride falls lower than humbleness,&rdquo; <mark>he had very great pride&mdash;pride in his ancestry</mark>. Indeed if he was not the son of God he certainly behaved himself as such. He talks of his father with undistinguished pride and of himself&mdash;&ldquo;the poor you have always with you but me you have not always with you.&rdquo; He doubts if he is the son of God and <mark>hates his people</mark>&mdash;the whited sepulchres&mdash;to<font color="green">[o]</font> much for deeds. <small> Stanislaus Joyce, <a name="SJJC" href="/udra/udex.htm#SJJC"><cite title="source">Complete Dublin Diary</cite></a> (manuscript: published 1971), 90</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
